.TH "work_on_cpu_safe" 9 "work_on_cpu_safe" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
work_on_cpu_safe \- run a function in thread context on a particular cpu
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" work_on_cpu_safe
.BI "(int cpu "  ","
.BI "long (*fn)(void *) "  ","
.BI "void *arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
the cpu to run on
.IP "fn" 12
the function to run
.IP "arg" 12
the function argument
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Disables CPU hotplug and calls \fBwork_on_cpu\fP. The caller must not hold
any locks which would prevent \fIfn\fP from completing.
.SH "RETURN"
The value \fIfn\fP returns.
